  24:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   ==============================================================================
  25:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****                      ##### How to use this driver #####
  26:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   ==============================================================================
  27:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   [..]
  28:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****       The RNG HAL driver can be used as follows:
  29:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\ccauXdwZ.s 			page 2


  30:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****       (#) Enable the RNG controller clock using __HAL_RCC_RNG_CLK_ENABLE() macro
  31:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****           in HAL_RNG_MspInit().
  32:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****       (#) Activate the RNG peripheral using HAL_RNG_Init() function.
  33:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****       (#) Wait until the 32 bit Random Number Generator contains a valid
  34:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****           random data using (polling/interrupt) mode.
  35:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****       (#) Get the 32 bit random number using HAL_RNG_GenerateRandomNumber() function.
  36:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  37:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     ##### Callback registration #####
  38:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     ==================================
  39:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  40:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
  41:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     The compilation define USE_HAL_RNG_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
  42:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
  43:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  44:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
  45:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     Use Function HAL_RNG_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback.
  46:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     Function HAL_RNG_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
  47:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : RNG Error Callback.
  48:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : RNG MspInit.
  49:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : RNG MspDeInit.
  50:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
  51:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     and a pointer to the user callback function.
  52:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  53:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
  54:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     Use function HAL_RNG_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
  55:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     weak (overridden) function.
  56:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     HAL_RNG_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
  57:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     and the Callback ID.
  58:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     This function allows to reset following callbacks:
  59:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : RNG Error Callback.
  60:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : RNG MspInit.
  61:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : RNG MspDeInit.
  62:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  63:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
  64:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     For specific callback ReadyDataCallback, use dedicated register callbacks:
  65:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     respectively HAL_RNG_RegisterReadyDataCallback() , HAL_RNG_UnRegisterReadyDataCallback().
  66:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  67:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
  68:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     By default, after the HAL_RNG_Init() and when the state is HAL_RNG_STATE_RESET
  69:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak (overridden) functions:
  70:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     example HAL_RNG_ErrorCallback().
  71:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
  72:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the HAL_RNG_Init()
  73:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     and HAL_RNG_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
  74:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_RNG_Init() and HAL_RNG_DeInit()
  75:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
  76:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  77:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
  78:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_RNG_STATE_READY state only.
  79:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
  80:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     in HAL_RNG_STATE_READY or HAL_RNG_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
  81:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
  82:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
  83:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     using HAL_RNG_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_RNG_DeInit()
  84:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     or HAL_RNG_Init() function.
  85:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
  86:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     [..]
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\ccauXdwZ.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     When The compilation define USE_HAL_RNG_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
  88:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     not defined, the callback registration feature is not available
  89:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****     and weak (overridden) callbacks are used.
  90:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c **** 
