 637:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   * @note   In the case of a clock error, the RNG is no more able to generate
 638:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         random numbers because the PLL48CLK clock is not correct. User has
 639:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         to check that the clock controller is correctly configured to provide
 640:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         the RNG clock and clear the CEIS bit using __HAL_RNG_CLEAR_IT().
 641:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         The clock error has no impact on the previously generated
 642:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         random numbers, and the RNG_DR register contents can be used.
 643:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   * @note   In the case of a seed error, the generation of random numbers is
 644:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         interrupted as long as the SECS bit is '1'. If a number is
 645:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         available in the RNG_DR register, it must not be used because it may
 646:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         not have enough entropy. In this case, it is recommended to clear the
 647:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         SEIS bit using __HAL_RNG_CLEAR_IT(), then disable and enable
 648:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         the RNG peripheral to reinitialize and restart the RNG.
 649:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   * @note   User-written HAL_RNG_ErrorCallback() API is called once whether SEIS
 650:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   *         or CEIS are set.
 651:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rng.c ****   * @param  hrng pointer to a RNG_HandleTypeDef structure that contains
